Elliotte Rusty Harold wrote:
&gt; Does anyone have handy a working example of the parameterized test case
&gt; pattern? My attempts to implement it keep failing in weird ways. There&#39;s
&gt; something I&#39;m just not getting about it. I&#39;m not sure how to work around
&gt; the lack of one of the two standard constructors.

_JUnit Recipes_, recipe 4.8. :) I fixed your example below.

&gt; Here&#39;s a simple sample data driven test that merely tests numbers are
&gt; positive:
&gt; 
&gt; import junit.framework.*;
&gt; import junit.textui.TestRunner;
&gt; 
&gt; public class DataDrivenTest extends TestCase{
&gt; 
&gt;     int i;
&gt; 
&gt;     public DataDrivenTest(int i) {
           setName(&quot;A test name so that it&#39;s not null... I usually 
require this in the constructor&quot;);
&gt;         this.i = i;
&gt;     }
&gt; 
&gt;     public static Test suite() {
&gt;         TestSuite result = new TestSuite();
&gt;         result.addTest(new DataDrivenTest(1));
&gt;         result.addTest(new DataDrivenTest(2));
&gt;         return result;
&gt;     }
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt;     public void testFoo() {
&gt;         assertTrue(i &gt; 0);
&gt;     }
&gt; 
&gt;     public static void main(String[] args) {
&gt;       TestRunner.run(suite());
&gt;     }
&gt; }
